##---------------------------------------------------------------------
@node CHANGES "Changes Log:"

                            @{b}>> Changes Log: <<@{ub}

Version changes prior to 1.0 (first public release) deleted.

Version Changes:
------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------
@REMARK lastver
1.6	The testing of the receiving email-address is now more strict when gating
	 F->U. So it should catch faulty addresses before SendMail does.
	Created SEEN-BY's with the @{" NODEADDRESS " LINK NODEADDRESS}, should have been @{" GATEADDRESS " LINK GATEADDRESS}.
	Rewrote some of the MIME routines to reduce size of AmiGate executable. :)
	Sometimes (very rare) AmiGate lost messages when gating from U->F.
	 This only happened if you were using @{" PACKETAPPEND " LINK PACKETAPPEND} and even then very
	 seldom. I have only seen it once. Anyway it is fixed now.
	@{" AUTOAREA " LINK AUTOAREA} has been changed to reflect GRn equivalent. Thus it is
	 much more useful.
	Hopefully fixed a bug related to @{" NEWSACTIVE " LINK NEWSACTIVE} that occurred on 2.0
	 machines only.
	PUBLIC 3 should now work in U->F direction too.
	Now converts tabs to spaces when gating U->F.
@REMARK endlastver

1.5	@{b}>> IMPORTANT NOTICE <<@{ub} The format of the @{" SENDMAIL " LINK SENDMAIL} config keyword has
	 changed!!! It will no longer append '-R "" <' automatically, so if you
	 are using AmigaUUCP 1.17 you'll have to change this. See @{" SENDMAIL " LINK SENDMAIL}
	 for details.
	Oops, the new @{" NEWSSERVER " LINK NEWSSERVER} keyword caused the mailing list keyword
	 MAILLIST to fail sometimes. Fixed.
	When gating F->U @{b}very@{ub} long lines (>10Kb) caused an Enforcer hit. Fixed.
	@{" DELETENEWSFROMUS " LINK DELETENEWSFROMUS} now works as intended.
	Added my config files for AmiTCP in the directory SampleCfg_AmiTCP.
	 See also @{" FAQ / Question 12 " LINK Q12}
	No longer makes a Newsgroup header if 'N' option is used in @{" AREA " LINK AREA}.
	If the Date: header was missing from an email/news file, AmiGate
	 generated an invalid PKT file. Fixed.
	The @{" GATEMAILBOX " LINK GATEMAILBOX} sometimes (very rare) garbled messages.
	New keyword @{" NOREPLYADDR " LINK NOREPLYADDR}.
	New keyword @{" NEWSACTIVE " LINK NEWSACTIVE}. Reads area definitions from an active
	 file. Saves you from having to maintenance two files.
	If the @{" GATENEWS " LINK GATENEWS} argument is used and no file is specified
	 input will be read from stdin. This is primarily for use with NNTPXfer.
	 See also @{" FAQ / Question 12 " link Q12}.
	New completely useless keyword @{" AUTOAREA " LINK AUTOAREA}.
	New keyword @{" PACKETAPPEND " LINK PACKETAPPEND}. Appends U->F messages to
	 existing packets. Useful with AmiTCP.

1.4	Last version released via the new version server. For further
	 information see @{" How to get new versions " LINK NEWVERSIONS}
	New keywords primarily for use with service providers like demon in
	 the UK: @{" NEWSSERVER " LINK NEWSSERVER}, @{" DELETENEWSFROMUS " LINK DELETENEWSFROMUS} and 'N' option in @{" AREA " LINK AREA}.
	The REPLYADDR kludge for mailing-lists is now set to the real posters
	 address. Don't know why I haven't done this before. Perhaps there
	 was a reason, so if this gives you any trouble let me know. :-)
	AmiGate will now continue with next newsbatch when encountering a
	 defective newsbatch (Eg. RNews out of synch). This means that it
	 will not stop when running unattended, but it also means that you
	 should check the log for errors every once in a while.
	The @{" GATEMAILBOX " LINK GATEMAILBOX} didn't delete its temporary file after processing.
	Multiple occurence of the same email-adresses are now allowed. Emails
	 sent U->F are simply gated to the first occurence. See @{" USER " LINK USER}
	Now using version 2.3 of MimeLite source.
	The "X-Z-F-TO:" and the "X-Comment-To:" headers are now examined when
	 gating news to echomail. The realname will be placed in the FidoNet
	 To: field.
	The header STRIP, PORT, KLUDGE comparison routine compared one
	 character less than it should. Fixed.
	The INTL kludge on letters being gated U->F used the @{" NODEADDRESS " LINK NODEADDRESS},
	 now uses @{" GATEADDRESS " LINK GATEADDRESS}.
	AmiGate will no longer choke on news-batches that has a "!# rnews"
	less than or equal to 0.
	Parsing of the FidoNet Origin: line made more tolerant.
	Corrupted newsbatches will be renamed to avoid reprocessing when
	 running unattended.

1.3a	Broke the @{" HEADERTEXT " LINK HEADERTEXT} routine in the last version. Fixed.

1.3	Now using version 2.2 of MimeLite source.
	Made the detection of invalid FidoNet packets more strict. AmiGate
	 will now stop processing FidoNet packets that are invalid.
	Fixed a rare bug in the FidoNet packet parsing routine caused by a
	 buffer being too small.
	Well, I just received some _very_ corrupted Usenet newsfiles, that
	 caused AmiGate to guru instantly. Added some "safety" code to help
	 fix these messages.
	The parsing of the From: line was buggy, fixed.
	Sometimes generated illegal FidoNet dates, fixed.
	Added some format specifiers to @{" HEADERTEXT " LINK HEADERTEXT} keyword.
	The X-To: header is now examined when gating news to echomail. The
	 realname will be placed in the FidoNet To: field.
	Added new @{" GATEMAILBOX " LINK GATEMAILBOX} CLI argument.
	Added new @{" AKASITE " LINK AKASITE} argument.
	Recompiled with SAS/C 6.55.

1.2	Changed the linebreak routine to force a break at column 79 instead
	 of 80. Should keep the gate at ibmmail.com from complaining.
	All I/O buffers are now set to 8 KB.
	New @{" DELETEUUCPNEWS " LINK DELETEUUCPNEWS} switch.
	Due to several requests the @{" MAXMSGSIZE " LINK MAXMSGSIZE} will no longer truncate
	 messages when gating U->F but split them instead.
	Somehow the USERNAME var remained set after AmiGate finished. Fixed.
	Added @{" NOQP " LINK NOQP} command line switch.
	Fixed a problem which caused invalid Message-ID: headers (Actually
	 bypassed is a better word for it, as the bug is in RawDoFmt()
	 pre v39)
	Removed the "Distribution: world" from the headers. If you miss it
	 use @{" HEADERTEXT " LINK HEADERTEXT} to generate it.
	Added public gating using site style addressing. See @{" PUBLIC " LINK PUBLIC}.
	Added new @{" GATENEWS " LINK GATENEWS} argument.
	Fixed the Origin length calculation routine.
	Added new @{" STATICORIGIN " LINK STATICORIGIN} keyword.
	Now accepts both full site qualification and local name only in the
	 control-files. Both "C rmail boble!brj" and 
	 "C rmail boble.ping.dk!brj" are valid.

1.1	Rewrote the detection of tearline and Origin line completely.
	 Should be bulletproof now. ;-)
	Enhanced detection of mailing-list's a bit.
	MSGID kludge from FidoNet messages will now be used to construct the
	 UUCP messageid header if present.
	Added arguments to PUBLIC keyword. See @{" PUBLIC " LINK PUBLIC}
	F->U gating code rewritten.
	Added code to detect invalid FidoNet packets.
	Added ++ and -- mapcode to @{" MAILLIST " LINK MAILLIST}. Will cause AmiGate to not look
	 for the To: and Cc: when deciding if an email is to a mailing list.
	Optimized the logfile writing.
	Now using version 2.1 of MimeLite source.
	Rewrote detection of To: and Cc:
	Added support for german ORIGID kludge: See @{" USEORIGID " LINK USEORIGID}
	Added @{" DLGMODE " LINK DLGMODE} to support DLG User.Data
	Cc: and Bcc: are now given to SendMail as headers instead of
	 arguments.
	REPLY kludge added to bounced messages.
	Mailing list messages U->F will now be sent to "All" instead of the
	 mailling list users real name. That will stop Spot from thinking all
	 messages are to you if you sign on to the mailing list using your own
	 userid.

1.0	First public release.
@endnode
